Now, OCA’s win-win decision last week seems to have set the stage for better diplomatic and economic relations between Doha, Riyadh and the Gulf in general.Sport, once again, has demonstrated its ability to unite the world, just as the famous “ping-pong diplomacy of the 1970s did in fostering good relations between China and USA through table tennis, or the 1914 “Christmas truce” football matches between Germany and Britain when the guns went silent. Last week, the Olympic Council of Asia (OCA) made an interesting decision on the hosts of the 2030 Asian Games that will transcend sport and help mend the fragile Gulf fabric.
Doha and Riyadh were the candidates to host the 2030 competition and engaged in aggressive campaigns on the back of political tensions between Qatar and Saudi Arabia.



