Hangzhou (China) will host the 2022 edition and Aichi-Nagoya (Japan) the 2026 Games.
In the run-up to last Wednesday’s vote, there was long-standing tension between Qatar and Saudi Arabia with the Saudis accusing Doha of aiding terrorism and backing the “unfriendly” Tehran government, with Riyadh subsequently mustering a regional blockade against the Qataris.
"Hosting the 2030 Asian Games has been a national priority for our country and so we are humbled and greatly honoured to have been awarded this prestigious event,” Doha 2030 chairman and Qatar Olympic Committee President Sheikh Joaan bin Hamad Al-Thani said after his city’s victory last week.



